hmmm....resetting offset and messageDigest makes this code fragile and hard to read. The flow of the code can be organized better as well. The whole block from line82 to line125 can be refactored like this:
offset = Files.size(saveToPath);
messageDigest = MessageDigest.getInstance(artifact.getAlgorithm());
if (offset > artifactSize) {
    deleteFile();
    downloadToFile(artifactFile, 0, artifactSize, messageDigest);
} else {
    // calculate the digest from the existing file
    updateExistingDigest(offset, messageDigest);
   // downloadToFile should handle the case when offset equals to the file size (just return)
   downloadToFile(artifactFile, offset, artifactSize, messageDigest);
}

Isn't this much simpler?

